        <section class="poem">
          <h2 class="title">Trigger</h2> 
          <p>I’m not comfortable here any longer.<br>
            Too predatory. Prehensile,<br>
            post-human.<br>
            Too liable to pull the trigger<br>
          at any given moment.</p>
          <p>I don’t sense<br>
            a civilized voice,<br>
            Or a song that makes you wonder<br>
            how it got this way.</p>
          <p>I was buffing the urns<br>
            when all this started.<br>
            Making my meager, minimum pay<br>
            pursuing ingrained despair.<br>
            I mean,</p>
          <p>Can you not look around<br>
            and see the obesity?<br>
            The pierced behemoth <br>
            we have become.</p>
          <p>Ashen, grey, ashes<br>
            lift, descend.<br>
            We are below noir,<br>
            Lost in a crowded substratum<br>
            where public services have run aground</p>
          <p>and the mayor’s on the take.<br>
            Everyone’s on the take. Even we<br>
            who usually wind up shoveling shit do so<br>
            awaiting our climb up the golden head of the idol.</p>
          <p>No one pokes you in the ribs anymore<br>
            unless it’s with a knife<br>
            or some sharp object<br>
            you smuggle off a plane.            </p>
         
        </section>
